paul l. reiber (born june 20, 1947) is the chief justice on the vermont supreme court. reiber graduated from hampden-sydney college in 1970 and from suffolk university law school in boston, massachusetts in 1974. reiber was in private practice in rutland until becoming a partner in kenlan, schweibert & facey in 1986. he was appointed by governor jim douglas as an associate justice in october 2003. gov. douglas swore him in as chief justice of the vermont supreme court on december 17, 2004.